<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> with panels within moulded edges on three sides (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.97</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.485</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.38</measure>).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the central panel.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.03-0.045</measure>; 12; ligatured <foreign lang="grc">ΗΝ</foreign> in I. 4; <term>sigma</term> lunate in 1. 1, otherwise rectangular.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0334" notAfter="0400">Mid to late fourth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<lg met="elegaic"><lb n="1"/><l><w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w lemma="σοφός">σοφὸν</w> <w lemma="ὅδε">ἥδε</w><lb n="2"/><rs type="subject" key="city"><w lemma="πόλις">πόλις</w></rs> <persName key="Eupeithius" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Εὐπείθιος">Εὐπείθιον</name></persName><lb n="3"/><w lemma="ἕνεκα">εἵνεκα</w> <w lemma="πᾶς">πάντων</w></l><lb n="4"/><l><w lemma="ἵστημι">στήσατο</w> <w met="LAI/NEOS2" lemma="λαίνεος">λαϊνέ<hi rend="ligature">ην</hi></w><lb n="5"/><w lemma="εἰκών">εἰκόνα</w> <w lemma="δέμω">δειμαμένη</w> <g type="leaf"/></l><lb n="6"/><l><w lemma="μνάομαι">μνωομένη</w> <w lemma="μετά">μετὰ</w><lb n="7"/><w lemma="πότμος">πότμον</w> <w lemma="ὅτι">ὅτ'</w> <w lemma="ἀνήρ">ἀνδρά<lb n="8" type="worddiv"/>σιν</w> <w lemma="αἶνος">αἶνος</w> <w lemma="ἀληθής">ἀληθὴς</w> <g type="leaf"/></l><lb n="9"/><l><w lemma="τίνω">τίνεται</w> <w lemma="ἀνδρόμεος">ἀνδρομέ<lb n="10" type="worddiv"/>ης</w> <w lemma="ἔκτοθι">ἔκτοθι</w> <w lemma="βασκανία">βασκα<lb n="11" type="worddiv"/>νίης</w> <g type="leaf"/></l>
</lg>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>This city had made and set up a stone image <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> the wise Eupeithios because of everything, recalling that it is after death that true praise, beyond human envy, is accorded to men.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="III.38">III.38</xref>.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p> <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath">Hadrianic baths</rs>: at the west side of trench A, in the room north of the tepidarium.</rs>  <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs> <rs type="lastLocation">Museum (1993).</rs>. </p></div>





<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Excavated by the NYU expedition in <date>1966</date> (<rs type="invNo">66.542</rs>; SBI <rs type="sbi">4</rs>). The plinth of the accompanying statue, with a fragment of a foot and the edge of a <term>chlamys</term> was found with the base.</p>
</div>

